description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Band 6 Occupational Health Advisor to join us at the Employee wellbeing Service at Barts Health&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fixed term contract to September 2021 .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you used to working to deadlines and have a good eye for detail, then this could be an opportunity to move your career forward and in a new direction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a varied role and you will have the opportunity to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross site&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility working from home&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have the opportunity to run walk in clinics (consulting with staff on their new roles and ensuring that they have the correct immunisations requirements).
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing immunisations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Phlebotomy and follow up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with Health surveillance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing a case load (management referrals)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is only a small part of the work around Occupational Health, as you will also be able to run projects, such as Travel Clinics, MOT clinics plus much more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is fixed term contract for 11 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in learning more about our team, please contact Sue Kennard on 02073774731&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
